article.description: Raul Frias scored a career-high 21 points, shooting 7 for 9 from behind the 3-point arc, Raiquan Clark added 16 points with a career-high 15 rebounds plus two steals and two blocks and LIU Brooklyn broke away after halftime to defeat Saint Peter's...
article.headline: Frias leads LIU Brooklyn in 74-58 defeat of Saint Peter's
article.linkText: Frias leads LIU Brooklyn in 74-58 defeat of Saint Peter's
article.story: NEW YORK -- Matthew Lee had 13 points off the bench to lead St. Peter's to a 69-58 win over Long Island-Brooklyn on Sunday. Hassan Drame had 13 points and 17 rebounds for St. Peter's (3-5). KC Ndefo added 7 points, eight rebounds and six blocks. Doug Edert and Daryl Banks III each scored nine. Raiquan Clark had 18 points and 12 rebounds for the Sharks (4-8). Ashtyn Bradley added 11 points. Ty Flowers had three blocks. St. Peter's matches up against Hampton on the road on Saturday. Long Island-Brooklyn faces Centenary (NJ) at home on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
